  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0db1\u0dc0 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dc3 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Marcos is sworn in as the new President of the Philippines",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ferdinand Romuildes Marcos was sworn in as the 17th President of the Philippines, pledging to prioritize food security in the country.",
        "The 64-year-old son of former President Ferdinand Marcos was sworn in at the National Museum in Manila before his 92-year-old mother Imelda and other family members.",
        "\"We prioritize the role of agriculture, the urgency of which is currently being ignored and misdirected,\" Marcos said after being sworn in as Minister of Agriculture.",
        "Over 15,000 police and security personnel have been deployed across the capital for the opening ceremony. Foreign dignitaries, diplomats and three former presidents of the Philippines, Fidel Ramos, Joseph Estrada and Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo attended.",
        "Marcos was received at the Presidential Palace by outgoing President Rodrigo Dutarte before the swearing-in ceremony.",
        "However, the Marcos administration will have to address a number of issues currently plaguing the Philippines, including rising unemployment, inflation, high debt service rates relative to gross domestic product (GDP), and rocketing gas and oil prices.",
        "Managing inflation is at the top of the list of things the president should do. Government data shows that 23.7% of the country's population of nearly 110 million lives in poverty."
      ],
